{
  "texts": [
    "Also worth noting are the performance of Meta's Llama 70B model and Mistral's Small model, which both had perfect semantic consistency despite having an imperfect, but notably high, consistency rate.",
    "In general, all models had a semantic consistency greater than 96% regardless of the consistency rate, which varied greatly between models from 0% to 100%.",
    "This implies that despite the models generating clinical notes written in a variety of ways, the meaning of the content of these notes was relatively consistent across multiple iterations.",
    "Thus, all models performed well in terms of intra-prompt stability.",
    "This implies that intra-prompt stability may be measured using semantic consistency alone than with consistency rate."
  ]
}